      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.townofrotterdam.gov/our-town/town-history"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "In 1942 Rotterdam adopted the Old World coat of arms and the motto ‘Sterker door Strijd,’ meaning ‘Stronger through Effort.’",
